  "texts": [
    "The typical factors undermining the effectiveness of DMHIs include low user engagement and low perceived credibility and usability; both of which are associated with poor treatment adherence and subsequently lower outcome, and the study type.",
    "The search terms were combinations of the keywords listed under Category 1, 2, & 3.",
    "To fulfill the objectives of this review, the inclusion criteria were (a) Randomized Controlled Trials (RCTs) or Clinical Trials or Pilot Studies or Feasibility Studies (b) of any kind of digital intervention (c) for individuals on waiting lists (d) for psychotherapy (e) with clear psychological outcome measurements that included depressive or anxiety symptoms.",
    "Two of the co-authors independently completed the title and abstract screening of the retrieved article records, as well as the full-text reviews of the eligible articles.",
    "The online platform Covidence was utilized in managing the screening process."
  ],
